$comment
  Hand-crafted VCD fixture for the Pro Gauge Cluster Stage widget.
  Drives four 8-bit gauges through normal, warning, and critical
  zones at known time-points. Used by the renderer integration test
  (cursor scrubbing) and by the verification doc as the demo file.

  Signal mapping (default 0–100 range):
    rpm   — gauge 0  — sweeps 0 → 50 → 78 (warn) → 95 (critical)
    temp  — gauge 1  — constant 30 → 70 (warn) → 88 (critical)
    volt  — gauge 2  — constant 50 (always normal)
    psi   — gauge 3  — error track: 50 → x (X-state at t=200)

  All signals are 8-bit unsigned wires interpreted as 0–255 by the
  reader; the gauge widget's min/max=0/100 maps the raw integer value
  one-to-one to the gauge's value space.
$end
$version Hand-crafted gauge_cluster_demo $end
$date 2026-05-04 $end
$timescale 1ns $end
$scope module top $end
$scope module gauges $end
$var wire 8 ! rpm $end
$var wire 8 " temp $end
$var wire 8 # volt $end
$var wire 8 $ psi $end
$upscope $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
$dumpvars
b00000000 !
b00011110 "
b00110010 #
b00110010 $
$end
#100
b00110010 !
#150
b01001110 !
b01000110 "
#200
b01011111 !
bxxxxxxxx $
#250
b01011111 !
b01011000 "
